<subSubSection id="F05061E6937ED7A0E605649538CD987B" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="14" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph id="76E895E85202236650E99AF426E9A538" pageId="14" pageNumber="39">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="02851011F125FFBC0696753883AC0CDA" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="14" pageNumber="39">
Perennial herbs, 1-2 m tall. Stems erect, conspicuously ribbed, villose. Leaves 15-20 by 5-8 cm, obovate or oblanceolate, margin serrate, apex acuminate, base cuneate, subcoriaceous; both surfaces scabrous with whip-shaped hairs and capitate glands; lateral veins 6-8-paired; petioles up to 10 mm long. Capitulescences terminal and axillary, paniculate. Capitula campanulate, 12-15 mm long, pedunculate. Receptacle flat, 2-2.5 mm in diam., hairy. Involucres campanulate, in 4-5 series, 7-8 mm long, 6-7 mm in diam., herbaceous. Phyllaries light green, margin piliferous, outer surface densely arachnoid, glands capitate; the outer and the middle ones ovate, apex spinose; the inner ones ovate-lanceolate, apex apiculate. Florets ca. 20; corollas 
<pageBreakToken id="20EC209F5E3F413DD879BFCFB43FFCD1" pageId="15" pageNumber="40" start="start">funnelform</pageBreakToken>
, purple, glandular; corolla tubes ca. 5 mm long; corolla lobes ca. 3 mm long. Anthers yellowish, ca. 3 mm long, apical appendage acute, base acute. Styles purple, 5-8 mm long, branches 1.5-2.5 mm long. Achenes subterete, 3.5-4 mm long, 10-ribbed, covered with sparse hairs and glands. Pappus bristles, the inner ones 6-7 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
